  48. void
  49. ‌caml_event_trace(code_t pc)
  50. {
  51.   struct ev_info *evi = caml_exact_event_for_location(pc);
  52.   if (evi == NULL)
  53.     return;

  55.   printf("[%02d] Event at PC:%ld, Def:%s, File: %s, Line: %d, Chars:%d-%d\n",
  56.      Caml_state->id,
  57.      (long) (pc - caml_start_code),
  58.      evi->ev_defname, evi->ev_filename,
  59.      evi->ev_lnum, evi->ev_startchr, evi->ev_endchr);
  60.   fflush (stdout);
  61. }

  63. ‌void caml_disasm_instr(code_t pc)
  64. {
  65.   char buf[256];
  66.   char opbuf[128];
  67.   int instr = *pc;
  68.   snprintf(opbuf, sizeof(opbuf), "%6ld  %s", (long) (pc - caml_start_code),
  69.            (instr < 0 || instr >= FIRST_UNIMPLEMENTED_OP) ?
  70.              "???" : names_of_instructions[instr]);
  71.   pc++;
  72.   switch(instr) {
  73.     /* Instructions with one integer operand */
  74.   case PUSHACC: case ACC: case POP: case ASSIGN:
  75.   case PUSHENVACC: case ENVACC: case PUSH_RETADDR: case APPLY:
  76.   case APPTERM1: case APPTERM2: case APPTERM3: case RETURN:
  77.   case GRAB: case PUSHGETGLOBAL: case GETGLOBAL: case SETGLOBAL:
  78.   case PUSHATOM: case ATOM: case MAKEBLOCK1: case MAKEBLOCK2:
  79.   case MAKEBLOCK3: case MAKEFLOATBLOCK:
  80.   case GETFIELD: case SETFIELD: case GETFLOATFIELD: case SETFLOATFIELD:
  81.   case BRANCH: case BRANCHIF: case BRANCHIFNOT: case PUSHTRAP:
  82.   case CONSTINT: case PUSHCONSTINT: case OFFSETINT: case OFFSETREF:
  83.   case OFFSETCLOSURE: case PUSHOFFSETCLOSURE:
  84.   case RESUMETERM: case REPERFORMTERM:
  85.     snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s %d\n", opbuf, pc[0]); break;
  86.     /* Instructions with two operands */
  87.   case APPTERM: case CLOSURE: case CLOSUREREC: case PUSHGETGLOBALFIELD:
  88.   case GETGLOBALFIELD: case MAKEBLOCK:
  89.   case BEQ: case BNEQ: case BLTINT: case BLEINT: case BGTINT: case BGEINT:
  90.   case BULTINT: case BUGEINT:
  91.     snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s %d, %d\n", opbuf, pc[0], pc[1]); break;
  92.     /* Instructions with a C primitive as operand */
  93.   case C_CALLN:
  94.     snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s %d,", opbuf, pc[0]); pc++;
  95.     /* fallthrough */
  96.   case C_CALL1: case C_CALL2: case C_CALL3: case C_CALL4: case C_CALL5:
  97.     if (pc[0] < 0 || pc[0] >= caml_prim_name_table.size)
  98.       snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s unknown primitive %d\n", opbuf, pc[0]);
  99.     else
  100.       snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s %s\n", opbuf,
  101.                (char *) caml_prim_name_table.contents[pc[0]]);
  102.     break;
  103.   case SWITCH:
  104.     snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s ntag=%lu nint=%lu\n",
  105.                  opbuf,
  106.                  (unsigned long) pc[0] >> 16,
  107.                  (unsigned long) pc[0] & 0xffff);
  108.     break;
  109.   default:
  110.     snprintf(buf, sizeof(buf), "%s\n", opbuf);
  111.   }
  112.   printf("[%02d] %s", Caml_state->id, buf);
  113.   fflush (stdout);
  114. }

  116. void
  117. ‌caml_trace_value_file (value v, code_t prog, asize_t proglen, FILE * f)
  118. {
  119.   int i;
  120.   fprintf (f, "%#" ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "x", v);
  121.   if (!v)
  122.     return;
  123.   if (prog && v % sizeof (int) == 0
  124.            && (code_t) v >= prog
  125.            && (code_t) v < (code_t) ((char *) prog + proglen))
  126.     fprintf (f, "=code@%ld", (long) ((code_t) v - prog));
  127.   else if (Is_long (v))
  128.     fprintf (f, "=long%" ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "d", Long_val (v));
  129.   else if (Stack_base(Caml_state->current_stack) <= (value*)v &&
  130.            (value*)v < Stack_high(Caml_state->current_stack))
  131.     fprintf (f, "=stack_%ld",
  132.              (long)((intnat*)Stack_high(Caml_state->current_stack)-(intnat*)v));
  133.   else if (Is_block (v)) {
  134.     int s = Wosize_val (v);
  135.     int tg = Tag_val (v);
  136.     int l = 0;
  137.     switch (tg) {
  138.     case Closure_tag:
  139.       fprintf (f, "=closure[s%d,cod%ld]",
  140.                s, (long) ((code_t) (Code_val (v)) - prog));
  141.       goto displayfields;
  142.     case String_tag:
  143.       l = caml_string_length (v);
  144.       fprintf (f, "=string[s%dL%d]'", s, l);
  145.       for (i = 0; i < ((l>0x1f)?0x1f:l) ; i++) {
  146.         if (isprint ((int) Byte (v, i)))
  147.           putc (Byte (v, i), f);
  148.         else
  149.           putc ('?', f);
  150.       };
  151.       fprintf (f, "'");
  152.       goto displayfields;
  153.     case Double_tag:
  154.       fprintf (f, "=float[s%d]=%g", s, Double_val (v));
  155.       goto displayfields;
  156.     case Double_array_tag:
  157.       fprintf (f, "=floatarray[s%d]", s);
  158.       for (i = 0; i < ((s>0xf)?0xf:s); i++)
  159.         fprintf (f, " %g", Double_flat_field (v, i));
  160.       goto displayfields;
  161.     case Abstract_tag:
  162.       fprintf (f, "=abstract[s%d]", s);
  163.       goto displayfields;
  164.     case Custom_tag:
  165.       fprintf (f, "=custom[s%d]", s);
  166.       goto displayfields;
  167.     default:
  168.       fprintf (f, "=block<T%d/s%d>", tg, s);
  169.     displayfields:
  170.       if (s > 0)
  171.         fputs ("=(", f);
  172.       for (i = 0; i < s; i++) {
  173.         if (i > 20) {
  174.           fputs ("....", f);
  175.           break;
  176.         };
  177.         if (i > 0)
  178.           putc (' ', f);
  179.         fprintf (f, "%#" ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "x", Field (v, i));
  180.       };
  181.       if (s > 0)
  182.         putc (')', f);
  183.     };
  184.   }
  185. }

  187. void
  188. ‌caml_trace_accu_sp_file (value accu, value * sp, code_t prog, asize_t proglen,
  189.                          FILE * f)
  190. {
  191.   int i;
  192.   value *p;
  193.   fprintf (f, "accu=");
  194.   caml_trace_value_file (accu, prog, proglen, f);
  195.   fprintf (f, "\n sp=%#" ARCH_INTNAT_PRINTF_FORMAT "x @%ld:",
  196.            (intnat) sp, (long) (Stack_high(Caml_state->current_stack) - sp));
  197.   for (p = sp, i = 0;
  198.        i < 12 + (1 << caml_params->trace_level) &&
  199.          p < Stack_high(Caml_state->current_stack);
  200.        p++, i++) {
  201.     fprintf (f, "\n[%ld] ", (long) (Stack_high(Caml_state->current_stack) - p));
  202.     caml_trace_value_file (*p, prog, proglen, f);
  203.   };
  204.   putc ('\n', f);
  205.   fflush (f);
  206. }
